    "intro": "Interpretation asks what the text *means* — moving from observation to the author's intent in its canonical and historical context. 2 Chronicles 17 is addressed to post-exilic Judah rebuilding after the Babylonian catastrophe; every detail of Jehoshaphat's faithfulness is simultaneously a description of the past and a prescription for the present. The movements below trace the chapter's argument from Jehoshaphat's personal piety through the teaching mission to the military and political flourishing that follows.",
